so xpo was the company selected to deliver the tv i ordered on amazon .. the day before thd deliver i received a call to remind me about the delivery. i also received a reminder via email.  i went on yelp to read the reviews the night before and based on what i read, i got really worried .. i really did expect the worst .. well the day arrived and i couldn't be more pleased.. the called 30 mins before ... arrived, unboxed the tv, installed the stand, plugged it in and left all within 15 mins .. so i wanted to at least come on here and put a positive review to help tell folks out there to relax a bit & give this company a chance.







ZERO ZERO ZERO--definitely not worth the one star (this company isn't even worth the chewed piece of gum stuck to the bottom of my shoe) but unfortunately it's the only rating option I have available!  PLEASE READ--RUN FOR THE HILLS if you hear the letters XPO out of any companies mouth for shipment/delivery because frankly it won't happen!!  

After 8+ days you will talk to countless "representatives" and supposed "supervisors" all of which will lie through their teeth and try and pass the buck to the next guy.  You may get lucky and get the occasional empty apology that wastes even more of your time because again they don't follow through with anything they say they will.  And please by any means don't hold your breath waiting for them to pick up their phones and contact you because that phone call will never come...any communication we have exchanged with this "company" was initiated by myself or my husband.

I'm not sure how a "company" that is run so poorly stays in business.  We are contemplating taking legal action against them for the atrocious customer service experience and fraudulent services that has led to a mountain of unnecessary distress.  Perhaps when they're in court under oath they'll have to tell the truth even if it strikes them dead right there!!







Lengthy discussion prior to delivery of a fridge via a Best Buy sales manager about hauling away a fridge 6 feet down a hall and relocating a fridge 5 feet up the hall, and hooking up the new fridge, charge $28. The sales mgr fails to indicate to XPO how to enter the gate. I confirm the delivery 1 day prior and reiterate I will need to be called to let them thru the gate. Staying home from work and reading previous bad reviews was anxiety producing, but nobody is prepping for brain surgery, and I am no fridge virgin.

XPO calls 30 minutes out - tailgates into the subdivision, rings doorbell, not following instructions yet. Am believer measure twice cut once. The man who would not give me his name is a hothead, unhinged does not begin to describe his Trump like behavior. He calls the warehouse with the intent of hauling off the old fridge but not delivering the new one that is sitting in the street. All the food I unloaded from the inoperable fridge is packed in ice for 1 more hour and then a smorgasbord for all. 

After 35 minutes of calls and his whining about his packet will get him in hot water, clueless about this ruining his day, it is his job to deliver appliances, and Best Buy is on the phone speaking not to the driver but to me saying make him deliver. He tells me now I will be required to sign a waiver. 

Not happening. I explain that I watched the movers put the fridges in the house and not one door had to be removed. Asked him to leave the new in line filter intact on the fridge being hauled off, he promptly cuts it in two, $35 blown, he is pissed. I am praying he is not packing. I offer him and his buddy who speaks little English a cold drink, he declines. Again he demands I sign a waiver as I will hold him accountable for the dings he is going to put in floors and walls.  I tell him go slow and no damage will occur. He does put the new fridge in the kitchen, refuses to install it and drives away, I had taken many photos while all of his antics were going on. 

He missed a good tip, hope he did not kick the dog when he got home. He refused to give me his name until he needed me to sign the completed delivery. 1.20 hours of lousy CS.

Hubs got on phone with Best Buy and Samsung getting instructions as to why the bad actor failed to hook up the fridge. Already done a Best Buy survey at their urgency, seems nobody has good luck with this outfit but they all use them, in the future supposedly Geek Squad will do all appliance installations. Won't repeat this scenario, life is too short.







If the option was zero stars that is what I'd pick. We are still in the middle of this nightmare. I attempted to replace a refrigerator for my tenant.  The existing frig is not cooling or freezing properly, Our first delivery attempt the delivery man from XPO Last Mile Courier. measured the space and said the frig would not fit.  He did not bring the frig up the stairs to the second floor. 
The frig is similar in size to the existing one.  I asked if the documented his measurements. 
Apparently not at least no record.  
After much measuring and discussion we decided to not risk keeping the the original purchase and pick a smaller frig.  So we purchase and wait for a call from XPO Last Mile Courier. They called that evening with 2 hour window.  They arrive after the estimated time unbox the frig and see it is damagaed with a big dent in the back side of the frig. The driver recommends we refuse delivery due to damage which we agreed to.  I return to the store for the third time.  The Ridder Park store did not have the same model in stock and recommend I go to the Newhall store because they had 4 in stock.  
Why couldn't it be ordered by the store I'm at?? No I  have to drive to the store...really same company but do not share inventory.  I drive to Newhall store purchase new frig then attempt to get refund from Newhall store.  NO I must drive back to the store I purchased the frig??? REALLY?? Are you separate stores?  YUPP  Not like sears or Home Depot. I will never make this kind or purchase a Lowes ever ever again.
BUT we're not done yet this frig still needs to be delivered to my tenant who is not so patiently waiting for a frig that will keep her food cold.  3 days later, eating out with her children. 
Now it's Saturday I get the call for delivery between 12 to 2pm on Sunday. Then I get another call changing time to 2pm to 4pm. Then they call tenant and tell her 2:30 to 4:30. At 4:18 they call are running behind schedule and no ETA. but GUARANTEED that it would be delivered today. Next call is cancelling deliver for that day.  Apparently they don't pay Over time. 
 But they will call on Monday in the PM with an ETA. 
At this point I'm attempted to cancel but my tenant needs a frig ASAP to add to all this she took one day off work to accept deliver that didn't happen. The biggest complaint is with XPO Last Mile Courier service but Lowes needs to take responbility for doing business with an unreliable company.
SURE WISH I HAD READ THIS EARLIER.







Horrible customer service!!! Very unprofessional!!!! they have delivered a washer machine to my house, and i specifically asked them before coming to my house to make sure to take off their shoes, or use those plastic covers for their shoes, because i have an infant baby crawling all over the house and i'm keeping it clean, and in the living room there is a light grey rag which i try to keep clean, because every stain or mark is noticeable. And they didn't listen to me, i wasn't home at the moment when they have arrived and they walked inside with shoes on, dirty shoes on and didn't even care. After i called them to ask why didn't they do what i asked, and they hanged up the phone and never answered back! Very rude and unprofessional!!!







Ordered washing machine from Lowe's in San Jose. Got a call the night before delivery that they would come at 6-8 pm on.... drum roll...... a Friday night, during Game 4 of the 2017 NBA Finals. I accepted anyways cause I really needed a washing machine.

Friday night rolls around, I'm watching the game and I waited, 6 pm nothing, 7 pm nothing, 8 pm nothing. 9 pm, nothing. Complete No Show. Totally disturbed the game as I tried to call Lowe's and XPO delivery.  

Called Lowe's the next day to find out that the delivery company couldn't find the item at Lowe's due to it being out of stock.They never called me about this as this is some vital information. I would have been waiting the entire weekend. I called XPO and they never answer the phone. At one point in time, I was on hold for an hour.

In the end, I went to pick it up myself at another Lowe's and just installed it myself. If you want something done right, do it yourself it seems. Horrible experience to say the least.







ZERO STARS. I purchased a refrigerator, washer and dryer from Lowe's. I actually purchased more expensive appliances specifically because they were in stock and guaranteed for delivery on Sunday instead of waiting a week. We just bought a house and needed a fridge, washer and dryer immediately, as there were none in the house. I get an automated call on Saturday saying delivery is confirmed for Sunday from 3:30 - 5:30pm. We frantically unpack to clear space for the appliances and 2:30 rolls around. I get another automated call saying delivery is now from 6:30 - 8:30 pm. Ok, fine. It gets to be 7:30 and I call XPO to make sure my delivery is still on track. We are living out of a cooler waiting on our new fridge, so we really need it that day. Chris (the customer service rep for XPO) says that, yes, the driver is still confirmed for delivery but that he had bad traffic (not unheard of in metro Atlanta, so I wasn't upset) and reassured me the delivery was still on track. Then 9:30pm rolls around and no show. I call back and was told the driver is "MIA all day" and "they don't know where he is, He's not answering his phone and they aren't sure if he has the delivery items or not." WHAT?! Are you telling me you actually don't know where your employee is, if he's got my items or not (THAT I ALREADY BOUGHT AND PAID FOR FROM LOWES), and that your excuse is "he's not answering his phone?" She then tells me that "he's probably not coming since it is 9:30 on a Sunday" and she can reschedule the delivery for Tuesday. The whole reason I purchased these specific appliances (at a higher cost than I would have paid for other models that could have been delivered Thursday) was because they were available for next day delivery. I explain this to her and say that Tuesday delivery is unacceptable. She then says "I'll talk to my manager" AND HANGS UP ON ME. I've spent the last 48 hours moving a house, unpacking boxes, and waiting on my delivery only to be unceremoniously hung up on after being told that their delivery driver essentially made off with my appliances and they don't know where he is. Fast forward to the next day, we go to the Lowe's store we bought them from and, big shocker here,THE APPLIANCES WERE RETURNED TO THE STORE AT 10:30 PM LAST NIGHT BY THE DELIVERY DRIVER. He literally made ZERO deliveries yesterday and just drove around with them in the truck all day and returned them to the store. Now Lowe's is telling me that the earliest they can deliver them is on Thursday, because "we have a lot of other deliveries to deal with and they are already scheduled." ARE YOU KIDDING?! Now we are renting a U-Haul and taking off work to pick up our appliances directly from the store. I'm not living out of a cooler for another 4 days. After multiple conversations with customer service, Lowe's has agreed to reimburse us for the cost of the truck rental and I'm still arguing with them about price matching us for the lower cost washer and dryer we wanted to purchase in the first place, but didn't since they wouldn't be delivered until Thursday...THE NEW DELIVERY TIME FOR OUR "GUARANTEED ON SUNDAY" delivery. XPO Logistics has the worst customer service from a company I have EVER experienced. Completely uncommunicative, no regard for your time or effort, and clearly I'm not the only one who has experienced this. From now on, if I ever have the need for delivery, I'll be asking each store who they contract with for delivery service. If it is XPO, I'll be shopping elsewhere. That's how bad they are.







