        7/6/2017
    

If apathy were an Olympic event, XPO would win the Gold Medal.Oh where do I begin. Let's start with the scorecard: 0-4. Out of four deliveries, XPO managed to find a unique way to mess up each and every one. I ordered various large pieces for a home solar project. The wholesaler had (no longer based on these events) an exclusive with XPO. Much like the cable company, XPO calls you prior and provides a time window to be available for delivery. Fair enough...can't fault them for that. However, I took time off to be available from the 3-6PM arrival...and nada. After 6PM I called to inquire. The response: "we had a new driver and he was afraid to come down your street". Sigh. Simple follow-up question I asked: "Is there a reason you didn't call to tell me this"? Their answer was essentially..."That's not my job". Seriously...zero effort to minimize my frustration. I eventually asked to speak to this gentleman's supervisor. He actually was quite good. He tracked down the error and made certain the shipment would arrive first thing between 8-11AM the next day. So...next day I waited...again...patiently from 8-11AM. Nada. Nothing. Zillch. Again, I called to inquire as to the whereabouts. This time, a different, yet equally dismissive customer service rep said, it would be delivered between 3-6PM, and whomever told me it would be between 8-11AM was wrong. Once again..."Is there a reason you didn't call to tell me this"? You guessed the answer..."That's not my job".The order did arrive. Intact. Hooray. The driver was polite and efficient. But I needed to make one more purchase/delivery. This time the order was scheduled again between 3-6PM. The timing was perfect...just one small problem...only half the order was there. The driver had no clue where the other half was. So I called XPO. I seemed to irritate them inquiring as to where the other half was. Their response was..."it's probably on a truck somewhere...but we won't know until some truck has one extra box leftover. Check back in a week." Meanwhile, I have workers whose very paycheck and lives depend on getting this order and proceeding with the project. There was zero empathy. Zero apology. It is as though they have a monopoly and you are simply at their mercy. So one week went by, and I heard nothing. I again called. They were able to find it in their warehouse (seemingly based only on my call). I arranged for shipping THE FOLLOWING DAY. Nope...a few hours later, there was a driver pounding on my unoccupied door. Fortunately, my solar installer was able to come over and sign on my behalf. We have several other projects that would involve XPO. We contacted our wholesaler, who is keeping track of such complaints, and has arranged to now also allow shipping via UPS. It may cost a fraction more...but it is so very worth it!




