XPO Logistics, Inc. Key Developments

XPO Logistics, Inc. Provides Earnings Guidance for the Second Quarter Ended June 30, 2017
Jul 17 17
XPO Logistics, Inc. provided earnings guidance for the second quarter ended June 30, 2017. For the period, the company expects total revenue of $3.755 billion to $3.765 billion, operating income of $183 million to $187 million, cash flows from operating activities of $205 million to $215 million and payments for purchases of property and equipment less proceeds from sale of assets of approximately $120 million. In addition, it estimates that it incurred depreciation and amortization expense of approximately $165 million.


XPO Seeks Acquisitions
Jul 17 17
XPO Logistics, Inc. (NYSE:XPO)  plans to make an offering of 11 million shares of its common stock in a registered underwritten offering. XPO expects to use the net proceeds from the sale of the shares of its common stock in this offering and any net proceeds it receives upon the future settlement of the forward sale agreements for general corporate purposes, which may include strategic acquisitions and the repayment or refinancing of outstanding indebtedness.


XPO Logistics Wins Contract from BrewDog
Jul 10 17
XPO Logistics announced that it obtained a contract from BrewDog. XPO will provide class-leading temperature-controlled warehousing for BrewDog's stockholding of craft beer at a multi-user, 125,000 square foot facility in Mossend, Scotland.


