IT Budget




XPO Logistics, Inc. provides transportation and logistics services.  Recent XPO acquisitions include Pacer International, New Breed, Con-way Inc., Bridge Terminal Transport, UX Specialized Logistics, Optima Service Solutions, and 3PD.  The company unified its operations and services under a single brand… MoreXPO Logistics, Inc. provides transportation and logistics services.  Recent XPO acquisitions include Pacer International, New Breed, Con-way Inc., Bridge Terminal Transport, UX Specialized Logistics, Optima Service Solutions, and 3PD.  The company unified its operations and services under a single brand in early 2015.

XPO acquired Con-Way in October, 2015, and is currently considering the sale of certain Con-way holdings.  XPO acquired a controlling interest in Norbert Dentressangle in June, 2015, and has merged the acquisition into its operations.
• XPO Logistics completed an acquisition of New Breed Inc. in June, 2014.
• XPO Completed an acquisition of Pacer International in April, 2014.

The IT department for XPO Logistics operates out of the several locations across the United States. The company… More• XPO Logistics completed an acquisition of New Breed Inc. in June, 2014.
• XPO Completed an acquisition of Pacer International in April, 2014.

The IT department for XPO Logistics operates out of the several locations across the United States. The company maintains IT staff at the Express-1 facility in Buchanan, MI, an operations center in Charlotte, NC, and a facility in Chicago, IL. The corporate headquarters is located in Greenwich, CT. The department is headed by a CIO, who is assisted by a CTO, who are based in the Charlotte Operations Center. 

Teams are responsible for the IT infrastructure, including telecommunications, IT security, and networks, IT resources, and business continuity.

The Application Development team works as the primary liaison for the company's XML-based .NET ERP, GPSNet. The team is also responsible for data extraction, validations, and evaluation, creating SOX auditing processes, developing of CRM and SharePoint, and creating an in-house training program on all products in the MS Office Suite, MS CRM, and MS SharePoint. 

Systems Administrators are responsible for system design, build, and deployment of server hardware and software components. They also manage multi-tiered application environments, including their design, implementation, and capacity/scaling challenges.





